{
  "stem": "19210.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were almost caught by the British on different occasions because there was a curfew from midnight till 6 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No one could be on the streets or on the highways.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we used to train, and we were caught once by a British patrol.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And fortunately enough, we were-- we were planning-- we already had our answers ahead of time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we-- we heard the-- that-- that command, halt, who is there or who goes there, then our lieutenant [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], later on became [NON-ENGLISH] Gal, G-A-L, he-- he answered the-- the British and told him, of course, that we were a-- a team of boxers training for an exhibition coming out.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we start to play boxing and all that, running, and doing like this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said, OK, and then they let us go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there was always some danger involved into that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And certainly during these trainings, we also provided escorts to convoys between Haifa and the Kiryat Motzkin-- Nahariyyah-Kiryat Motzkin, Kiryat Motzkin-Nahariyyah, you know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in each-- in each one of the vehicles-- it was a bus, a truck, a car, a motorcycle-- there was always someone from the Haganah, in most cases unarmed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only the [HEBREW], the [HEBREW], the lieutenant, would have some kind of a small gun, small arm, to help in case of need-- attack by the Arabs and so forth, which had happened on many occasions.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Several of the Jewish people from Nahariyyah that I knew were caught in-- in the city of Akko, and they were killed just before the action starts, because there was already tension mounting, you know.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Ultimately, the Arabs, they closed the city of Akko, so you couldn't even go home.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
